President Obama has declared a major disaster in California due to severe winter storms, flooding, and debris and mud flows that occurred from December 17, 2010, to January 4, 2011. Federal aid will be provided to supplement recovery efforts in the affected areas. The funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Sandy Coachman has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for the recovery operations. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.